The paper discusses the development of an integrated development environment (IDE) for answer-set programming (ASP), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) and programming languages (PL). The paper also mentions the use of new support techniques that meet the constraints of practical applicability, which suggests a focus on software engineering (SE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of external solvers and visualisation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (LG) and systems and control (SY).
